Added annyang.trigger() command

Simulates speech being recognized.
This will trigger the same events and behavior as when the Speech
Recognition detects speech.

Can accept either a string containing a single sentence, or an array
containing multiple sentences to be checked in order until one of them
matches a command (similar to the way Speech Recognition Alternatives
are parsed)

Examples:
````javascript
annyang.trigger('Time for some thrilling heroics');
annyang.trigger(
    ['Time for some thrilling heroics', 'Time for some thrilling
aerobics']
  );
````

Don't restrict usage to a certain vendor prefix

Don't restrict usage to a certain vendor prefix

Make the library work with all browsers that implemented (correctly)
the Web Speech Recognition API, not just the ones that use the webkit
prefix.

This way of using the Speech Recognition API is more practical, espe-
cially as browsers are moving away from vendor prefixes and start using
a flag like mechanism, thus using only the unprefixed version.

http://www.chromium.org/blink/developer-faq#TOC-Will-we-see-a--chrome--vendor-prefix-now-
